 <a href="/cgi-bin/LawCite?cit=%282001%29%2011%20Duke%20Journal%20of%20Comparative%20and%20International%20Law%20249" title="View LawCiteRecord" class="autolink_findcases">(2001) 11 <i>Duke Journal of Comparative and International Law </i>249</a>; Hodges,
above n 4, chs 1&#8211;8;  Alberta Law Reform Institute, above n 25, paras
86&#8211;87; Robyn Trigge, 'Representative Actions
under the Uniform Civil
Procedure Rules'  <a href="/cgi-bin/LawCite?cit=%282001%29%2021%20Queensland%20Lawyer%20110" title="View LawCiteRecord" class="autolink_findcases">(2001) 21<i> Queensland Lawyer </i>110</a>, 111.</p>
<p><sup><a name="fn28" href="#fnB28">[27]</a></sup> 	Andrews, above n 26,
249.</p>
<p><sup><a name="fn29" href="#fnB29">[28]</a></sup> 	See Lord Woolf, <i>Access
to Justice: Final Report</i> (1996), ch 17; Lord Chancellor's Department,
<i>Multi-Party Situations: Draft Rules and Practice Direction</i> (June
