<p>even where threshold tests are satisfied at the commencement of a class
action, Australian courts will be willing to entertain a Section
33N strike-out
application later in the proceedings. In this sense, after the issues in dispute
have been properly clarified, Section
33N provides courts with an 'escape hatch'
through which the issues may pass in order to terminate inappropriate class
actions.</p>
